text:
'Cangjie programming language_struct_define_struct_definition': 'In Cangjie code language, Structs in Cangjie are defined using the struct keyword, followed by the struct name and a body enclosed in curly braces. The body can contain member variables, properties, static initializers, constructors, and member functions.'

Code_Example:
struct Rectangle {
    let width: Int64
    let height: Int64
    public init(width: Int64, height: Int64) {
        this.width = width
        this.height = height
    }
    public func area() {
        width * height
    }
}

'Cangjie programming language_struct_define_struct_static_initializer': 'In Cangjie code language, Static initializers in structs are defined using the static init keyword. They are used to initialize static member variables. A struct can have at most one static initializer.'

Code_Example:
struct Rectangle {
    static let degree: Int64
    static init() {
        degree = 180
    }
}

Error_case_code:
struct Rectangle {
    static let degree: Int64
    static init() {
        degree = 180
    }
    static init() { // Error, redefinition with the previous static init function
        degree = 180
    }
}

'Cangjie programming language_struct_define_struct_constructors': 'In Cangjie code language, struct supports two classes of constructors: normal constructors and main constructors.
The common constructor starts with the keyword init, followed by the parameter list and the function body, and the initialization of all uninitialized instance member variables must be completed in the function body (if the parameter name and the member variable name cannot be distinguished, you can use this in front of the member variable to distinguish it, this represents the current instance of the struct), otherwise the compilation error will be reported.
Multiple normal constructors can be defined in a single struct, but they must constitute an overload (see Function Overloads), otherwise the weight is defined incorrectly.'

Code_Example:
struct Rectangle {
    let width: Int64
    let height: Int64
    public init(width: Int64) {
        this.width = width
        this.height = width
    }

    public init(width: Int64, height: Int64) { // Ok: overloading with the first init function
        this.width = width
        this.height = height
    }

    public init(height: Int64) { // Error, redefinition with the first init function
        this.width = height
        this.height = height
    }
}

'Cangjie programming language_struct_define_struct_member_functions': 'In Cangjie code language, Member functions in structs can be instance member functions or static member functions. Instance member functions are accessed through struct instances, while static member functions are accessed through the struct type name. Static member functions cannot access instance member variables or call instance member functions.'

Code_Example:
struct Rectangle {
    let width: Int64 = 10
    let height: Int64 = 20
    public func area() {
        this.width * this.height
    }
    public static func typeName(): String {
        "Rectangle"
    }
}
